projectUrl: https://www.kenny.cx
imageAlt: kenny.cx personal site screenshot
description: kenny.cx is my personal portfolio site, built to highlight the creative and technical work I have done over the years, from custom themes and tools to experiments that started as simple ideas and grew into something worth sharing.
summary: My personal portfolio site, built with 11ty.
---

<section class="py-md-6 py-5">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="mb-5">
            <p class="lead fw-normal">{{ description }}</p>
            <div class="d-grid col-12 col-sm-5 col-md-4 col-lg-3 col-xl-2">
                <a href="{{ projectUrl }}" class="btn btn-stckr" title="Visit project website: {{ projectUrl }}">
                    <i class="bi-globe2"></i> &nbsp;
                    Visit project website
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="grid g-4 g-md-5 mb-4">
            <div class="g-col-12 g-col-md-6 g-col-xl-4">
                <div class="d-flex h-100">
                    <div class="text-stckr me-4">
                        {% include "svg/11ty.njk" %}
                    </div>
                    <div class="d-flex-flex-column">
                        <p class="h5 fw-bold lh-base">Why 11ty?</p>
                        <p class="m-0">I chose Eleventy (11ty) because it’s fast, flexible, and lets me build exactly the kind of site I want—without getting in my way. Its simplicity and power make it perfect for a creative portfolio.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="g-col-12 g-col-md-6 g-col-xl-4">
                <div class="d-flex h-100">
                    <div class="text-stckr me-4">
                        {% include "svg/bootstrap.njk" %}
                    </div>
                    <div class="d-flex flex-column">
                        <p class="h5 fw-bold lh-base">Why Bootstrap?</p>
                        <p class="m-0">I use Bootstrap because it gives me a solid, responsive grid and a ton of utility classes—so I can focus on design and content, not reinventing the basics.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="g-col-12 g-col-md-6 g-col-xl-4">
                <div class="d-flex h-100">
                    <div class="text-stckr me-4">
                        {% include "svg/nunjucks.njk" %}
                    </div>
                    <div class="d-flex flex-column">
                        <p class="h5 fw-bold lh-base">Why Nunjucks?</p>
                        <p class="m-0">Nunjucks lets me write templates that are clean, readable, and reusable. It’s powerful enough for complex layouts, but simple enough to keep everything maintainable.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mb-5">
            {% set heroImage = projectId | assetImagePath('png', '', tags, 'lg') %}
            <img src="{{ heroImage | url }}" class="img-fluid rounded shadow-sm h-100"
                alt="{{ imageAlt or (title ~ ' screenshot') }}">
        </div>
        {% include "components/gallery.njk" %}
        <p>
            <a href="{{ '/projects' | url }}" class="btn btn-outline-stckr btn-sm">
                <i class="bi-arrow-left"></i> &nbsp;
                Back to all projects
            </a>
        </p>
    </div>
</section>